I believe so, yes.
I gave both the CI and student a directive to identify 1-2 things for each patient. Follow up on these two things, especially the "why" and be able to go back and address these.
1. Why did you do this in the history?
2. Why did you look at this area on this knee patient versus the other knee patient?
3. Why did you chooose this specific exercise for this lower leg patient but you didn't use that one with another leg patient?
